
Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I go to Page 04 of Thoracic CT

When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Mass' from the dropdown menu
Then 'I describe' box is enabled and automatically selected
And 'I know' box is enabled
And 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Characterization I' tab is enabled and automatically selected
And 'Characterization II' tab is enabled
And 'Differential diagnosis' tab is enabled

When I am on 'Characterization I' tab
Then 'Upper mediastinum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Lower mediastinum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Size' input field is enabled
And '2nd plane' input field is enabled
And '3rd plane' input field is enabled

And 'Well-defined' radio button is enabled
And 'Ill-defined' radio button is enabled
And 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Fat isodense (approx. - 100 HU)' radio button is enabled
And 'Liquid isodense ( > 0 HU)' radio button is enabled
And 'Soft tissue isodense' radio button is enabled

And 'Fat' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cysts' checkbox is enabled
And 'Calcification' checkbox is enabled
And 'Capsule' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fibrous septa' checkbox is enabled
And 'Liquid-fat level' checkbox is enabled
And 'Tooth/bone position' checkbox is enabled
And 'Necroses' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Lower mediastinum' checkbox
Then 'Anterior mediastinum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Middle mediastinum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Posterior mediastinum' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Calcification' checkbox
Then 'Diffuse' radio button is enabled
And 'Central' radio button is enabled
And 'Eccentric' radio button is enabled
